network_overview: The capture contains two independent IMS VoLTE/VoNR registration-only exchanges (no calls) between a UE-side P-CSCF (10.235.69.1) and two different core S-CSCFs (10.235.68.68 & 10.235.68.65) carried over SCTP/5060; all SIP procedures completed with 200 OK, so the control-plane is functionally healthy.

observations.finding: Only 6 packets in 240 ms – trace is extremely short and covers just two registration dialogs; no user-plane RTP or tunnel setup observed
Zero media streams present; no RTP/RTCP or packet-loss/jitter metrics can be assessed
Second registration uses a different server IP (10.235.68.65) and port (6408), suggesting pool-based CSCF redundancy – good resilience design

recommendations.action: Enable longer capture window (>5 s) that includes an actual VoLTE call to validate RTP bearer setup, GTP-U path and QoS enforcement
recommendations.rationale: Registration success alone does not prove end-to-end voice service; need to see SIP INVITE/183/200 with SDP, followed by RTP and RTCP

recommendations.action: Verify that SCTP multi-homing is configured on P-CSCF toward at least two S-CSCF IPs for higher availability
recommendations.rationale: Already seeing two different CSCF IPs; formal multi-homing will give hit-less fail-over on link loss

recommendations.action: Collect Diameter traces (Cx/Rx) concurrently to confirm successful PCRF QoS rule provisioning for the voice APN
recommendations.rationale: Ensures that VoLTE bearers receive the correct QCI=1/5 and bit-rate settings when a call is attempted

session_analysis.signaling_health: SIP registration completed successfully (100 Trying → 200 OK) on both flows; no re-transmissions or 4xx/5xx responses observed – control-plane is stable.
session_analysis.user_plane_health: No GTP-U tunnels set up; no RTP/RTCP packets captured – data-plane remains idle because no call was initiated.
session_analysis.voice_quality: No active voice session; therefore no MOS, packet-loss or jitter data available. IMS registration success implies UE is ready for calls.
session_analysis.cross_plane_correlation: Signaling plane (SIP/SCTP) is independent here; when a call starts the SDP in SIP will trigger EPS/5GS bearer creation (GTP-U) and RTP will flow on the user-plane – correlation can only be checked in a call-inclusive trace.
